    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah, the latency thing is one thing, but if we move to stateless lambdas, the 'agent_runtime' becomes obsolete. basically, the whole thing would just be a bunch of small scripts instead of a continuous agent running in the background. once we merge this, the agentic framework isn't really needed anymore. do you think there's any way to integrate the framework's core logic into those new functions, or would they essentially replace the need for you entirely?",
